61
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:32,880
Babes, I have a surprise for you today.

62
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,280
Today, I'm going to have all of you

63
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:38,080
switch dance partners continuously.

64
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:41,200
By switching partners throughout the lesson,

65
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,600
you'll learn

66
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,320
to trust and feel more confident

67
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,640
with your dance partner,

68
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,600
no matter who that person is.

69
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,520
Alright then,

70
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,440
let's start by pairing up first.

71
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,360
Get into your starting position.

72
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,240
Let's start.

73
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,280
And while you're dancing,

74
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,400
listen to me very carefully

75
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,520
I'll give you a signal

76
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,600
when it's time to switch partners.

77
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,000
Okay, babes?

78
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:02,800
Alright,

79
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,240
everyone, listen carefully for my signal.

80
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,080
As soon as I give the signal,

81
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,880
switch partners immediately.

82
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,280
Ready? Count.

83
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,240
One.

84
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,080
Two.

85
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:11,920
Three.

86
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,480
Go.

87
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,240
One, two, three.

88
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,960
One, two, three.

89
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:20,040
Have you found time to clear

90
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,120
things up with him?

91
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:23,360
Gap.

92
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,120
It's up to you.

93
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:29,320
Whatever you want.

94
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,400
Alright, switch partners.

95
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,159
Ready?

96
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:47,720
Count.

97
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,200
One, two, three.

98
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,680
One, two, three.

99
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,560
One, two, three.

100
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,159
If you're ready, then...

101
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,520
Switch partners.

102
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,720
Okay, everyone, switch partners.

103
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:06,160
Feel confident and smart.

104
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,560
P'Jane.

105
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,160
What are you doing?

106
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,240
Hold on to me tightly.

107
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,160
Otherwise, the dance won't look good.

108
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,880
One, two, three.

109
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:28,680
One, two, three.

110
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,440
What are you doing?

111
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,280
I'm not doing anything.

112
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,840
Liar.

113
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:45,200
I'm just doing the move the instructor taught us.

114
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,720
Unless you're hoping I'll do something else.

115
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,640
Your eyes are giving you away.

116
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,200
They say you want me to do that.

117
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,080
But if you don't want me to do this,

118
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,600
then ask me.

119
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:31,240
(Thanapat Piboonosot)

120
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,000
Hello.

121
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,920
Why are you here?

122
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,760
I'm here to buy medicine.

123
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:12,960
What do you need?

124
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:18,520
The medication set you gave me before has run out.

125
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,120
But I still haven't recovered.

126
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:23,480
Lately, it's been happening

127
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,800
more often than before.

128
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,520
What game are you playing now?

129
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,320
I'm telling the truth.

130
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,560
But I guess you don't believe

131
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,800
anything I say anymore.

132
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,000
Because you've lied to me before.

133
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,200
You can think of me that way.

134
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:06,000
But what if I'm not lying this time?

135
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,080
What are you going to do then?

136
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,960
Are you really going to leave me like this

137
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,120
and do nothing?

138
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,320
I'll prepare the medicine my dad recommended.

139
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,200
Thank you.

140
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:43,200
For still believing me and caring about me.

141
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:46,600
In that case,

142
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,760
I'll become a regular customer here.

143
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:58,400
That's enough.

144
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,400
Stop bothering me.

145
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:05,320
Didn't you tell me before

146
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:06,880
that if anything happened to me,

147
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,080
I could come here anytime?

148
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,720
Why won't you look at me?

149
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,560
Or are you afraid that if you do,

150
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,760
you'll feel something?

151
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:24,520
Because he doesn't want to

152
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:25,560
see your face anymore.

153
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,560
Stop bothering Jane.

154
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:38,440
And what right do you have over Jane

155
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:42,000
to tell me I can't talk to him?

156
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,200
Take your hand off.

157
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:09,280
Hey!

158
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,280
Both of you, stop!

159
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,520
Stop fighting!

160
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,120
Hey.

161
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:18,360
I'm hungry.

162
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:20,000
Should we order some pizza?

163
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:30,920
I'll come back another time.

164
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,160
I'm not hungry.

165
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,280
I'm not in the mood to eat either.

166
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:45,800
Yeah.

167
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,280
That's what I thought.

168
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,440
How did you get here, P'Dan?

169
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,840
I was worried about you.

170
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:06,040
So I asked Put for your address.

171
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:08,240
I didn't expect to run into him here.

172
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,120
Good thing I came today.

173
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,720
He's not really sick.

174
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,760
I don't know what to do

175
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,640
to stop him from bothering me.

176
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,280
What about you?

177
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,160
Have you come to peace

178
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,720
with not being with him?

179
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:56,040
There will be a day.

180
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,360
And until then,

181
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,400
if I ask to be the one who

182
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,000
protects you from him,

183
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,160
what would you say?

184
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:11,640
Hey!

185
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:14,240
Why is Little Jane with someone else?

186
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:15,800
Why isn't he here with P'Jane?

187
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,079
Don't tell me they broke up.

188
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,359
They seemed so in love.

189
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:22,880
Always going everywhere together.

190
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,599
That sucks.

191
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,320
Well...

192
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,600
If you need any help from me

193
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:46,560
just call.

194
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:17,280
I'm sorry

195
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:19,920
for not believing you.

196
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,200
You can punch me back.

197
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:46,480
Hey!

198
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,160
I'm just kidding.

199
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,200
Damn!

200
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:56,400
I was tensed up waiting for the punch.

201
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,200
Your face was pretty funny.

202
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,160
Huh?

203
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:04,400
I see you're getting along well with P'Dan.

204
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:05,800
I'm relieved.

205
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,040
Come on.

206
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:09,520
Let's go!

207
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,400
Would you like a brochure?

208
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,920
Would you like a brochure?

209
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:32,960
P'Dan told me that

210
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,200
he's going to put these photos

211
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:35,600
in an exhibition.

212
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:37,280
Did he invite you?

213
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,520
Not yet.

214
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,360
P'Dan knows photography too?

215
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:46,680
Yeah.

216
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:48,560
He may not look like it,

217
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,360
but he's got an artistic side to him.

218
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:19,680
Is it too heavy?

219
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,440
Hey. Actually,

220
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,320
you don't have to help me.

221
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:26,720
I can handle it.

222
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:29,160
I wanted to thank you

223
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,400
for helping me with so much.

224
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,200
The photos in the exhibition,

225
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:37,680
I'm going to let people buy them too.

226
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:39,720
The money will go to the club.

227
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:42,120
I had no idea

228
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,560
that you liked taking photos.

229
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,880
The reason I like photography

230
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:50,840
is because it lets me

231
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:54,120
capture how I saw the world at that moment.

232
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,560
I think I understand.

233
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,600
For me, it's drawing.

234
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,440
Really?

235
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,400
Have you ever thought about

236
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,240
submitting your work

237
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,240
for an exhibition or a competition?

238
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:14,800
I did think it about.

239
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,440
But not anymore.

240
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:29,840
Jane.

241
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,240
Try standing over there.

242
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,800
No way.

243
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:34,680
Come on.

244
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:35,960
It'll only take a sec. P'Dan.

245
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,240
Like a candid shot.

246
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:38,880
Come on.

247
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:40,200
Stand right here.

248
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,480
Natural?

249
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:43,080
Yeah, just pretend you don't notice.

250
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:45,200
Natural, okay?

251
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:46,280
One...

252
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,200
Alright, natural.

253
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:50,520
Is it ok?

254
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,400
Yeah.

255
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:52,960
Keep going.

256
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:54,800
Hey, try looking over there.

257
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,280
Hey.

258
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,000
Is that a real flower, P'Dan?

259
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:04,400
Maybe it has to be a bit fuller.

260
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:08,880
Here.

261
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:10,280
Thank you.

262
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,120
Uh, P'Dan.

263
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:16,000
The exhibition concept,

264
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,440
The colors

265
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,160
that remain.

266
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:21,800
Ah..

267
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,360
What does it mean?

268
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:24,480
Well..

269
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:27,600
It's black-and-white street photography.

270
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:30,000
But they're photos that still feel colorful

271
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
even though they're black and white.

272
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:36,120
Actually, here's a better example.

273
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:41,200
I take a picture of the sky.

274
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,560
And then..

275
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,000
Here.

276
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:50,080
We try to turn it into black and white.

277
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:54,000
Even so, you can still imagine

278
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,160
that it blue.

279
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:57,760
Oh.

280
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,000
I get it now.

281
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,400
Hey, do you like this one?

282
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,000
Do you like this photo?

283
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:07,840
Hey.

284
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:10,880
Yeah, I do.

285
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:12,840
I look better than in real life.

286
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,600
Can I keep these photos?

287
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,000
Let me edit it first and I'll send it to you.

288
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:21,640
Okay.

289
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:25,400
Here.

290
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:26,760
Let's take a photo.

291
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,440
Whoa.

292
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,080
Very Gen Z.

293
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:31,080
Okay.

294
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,080
Okay.

295
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,880
Let me take you home.

296
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:51,160
Sure.

297
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,520
Are you interested in me?

298
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,280
Since when?

299
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:32,200
Well...

300
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:34,880
There was a time when

301
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:36,320
I stopped playing football, right?

302
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,520
And when I came back to practice,

303
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,600
you encouraged me.

304
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:45,320
That's all?

305
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:47,520
It's just...

306
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,320
I don't know if you remember it, but...

307
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:52,680
to me,

308
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:56,120
your encouragement meant a lot.

309
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,880
It helped me really get back to myself.

310
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,760
Yeah...

311
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,080
Let's go.

312
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,080
Hello.

313
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:30,120
Oh.

314
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:30,880
Hello.

315
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:31,760
Hello.

316
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:32,560
Hi.

317
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:35,240
Everyone,

318
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,520
this is P'Dan.

319
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,080
He's a senior from my university.

320
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,680
I invited him to have dinner at our house.

321
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,360
Wait... This isn't P'Big Jane.

322
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:48,840
Jean.

323
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,160
Uh..

324
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,720
Make yourself at home.

325
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:00,160
Jane called and told us to prepare extra food.

326
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:05,560
Yes, ma'am.

327
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,080
Shall we go eat, Mom?

328
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,040
Uh, sure.

329
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:11,560
Come on.

330
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:12,720
Let's get the food ready.

331
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,440
They're definitely not just friends.

332
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:15,720
Excuse me.

333
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,920
Are you closed yet?

334
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,040
Oh.

335
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:22,200
Not yet. You can still order.

336
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,920
Half a tael of sliced ginseng.

337
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,240
100 grams of Chinese yam, please.

338
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,240
Oh.

339
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:27,720
Jane.

340
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,000
Could you do it?

341
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:31,600
Sure, Dad.

342
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:32,880
Ah..

343
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:33,880
Come on.

344
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:34,400
Jean.

345
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:36,400
Help me set the table.

346
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:37,640
Okay.

347
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:43,240
Make yourselves comfortable.

348
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,320
Do you need any help?

349
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:50,960
Do you know how?

350
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,560
I've never done it before.

351
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:56,400
But I'd like to try.

352
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:02,160
Here, P'Dan.

353
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:37,680
Here.

354
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:40,520
Thank you.

355
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,440
Mom.

356
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:45,400
Oh.

357
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:46,400
Thank you.

358
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:47,720
You're welcome.

359
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,000
Wow.

360
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,280
You're good at this.

361
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:54,440
Next time, you can come help us at the shop.

362
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:55,760
Mom...

363
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:56,840
In that case,

364
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,840
I'll stop by and help more often.

365
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,280
You said it.

366
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,400
If everything's ready, let's go eat.

367
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,400
Is there anything else I can help with?

368
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,880
Just a little, help carry the drinks please.

369
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,280
Okay, I'll do that.

370
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:12,640
Come here, dear.

371
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:22,360
I'll carry the food.

372
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,800
Then I'll help carry it.

373
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,200
It's hot.

374
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:29,640
Oh, it's fine.

375
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:03,480
P'Jane.

376
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:04,640
P'Jane.

377
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:08,360
What is it?

378
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,320
What?

379
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:15,200
P'Jane.

380
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:16,320
It's just that...

381
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:19,080
Can I borrow some money?

382
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:21,960
I need to pay for my school's sports day expenses.

383
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,920
I don't want to bother Mom and Dad.

384
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:26,720
I'll pay you back as soon as the event is over.

385
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,360
Why?

386
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:30,960
How much do you need?

387
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:37,440
Fifty thousand.

388
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:38,320
Huh?

389
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:39,600
Fifty thousand?

390
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:41,280
Keep your voice down.

391
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:43,480
Why are you being so loud.

392
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:48,560
What kind of sports day costs fifty thousand baht?

393
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,280
What are you even spending it on?

394
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:57,320
Jane.

395
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:00,800
Your mom is asking for you.

396
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:15,800
Is something going on?

397
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:41,800
They're all beautiful.

398
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,080
So...

399
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,800
Where are your photos?

400
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,160
They're inside.

401
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:52,200
This whole section is mine.

402
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:53,520
Wanna take a look?

403
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:05,760
Oh, look at this.

404
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:06,760
So cute, right?

405
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:07,520
You're right.

406
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:08,080
Yeah.

407
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,000
Oh, this photo is so cute.

408
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:11,000
Yeah.

409
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,040
Overall..

410
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,360
The compostion is great honey.

411
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:17,080
Uh...

412
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,440
He really put a lot of effort into these.

413
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:19,800
Yeah.

414
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,200
I wanted to surprise you.

415
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,120
That's why I didn't tell you beforehand.

416
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:33,320
What?

417
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:35,520
To me,

418
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,600
your black-and-white photos

419
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:41,800
can't hide the colors that exist inside you.

420
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,800
You brought color into my life.

421
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:46,680
You made it feel alive

422
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:50,320
in a way I've never felt before.

423
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,160
Isn't that the person in the photo?

424
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,760
Really? It is.

425
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,560
Oh my God.

426
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,800
This one is 3,500 baht.

427
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:08,000
That's too expensive.

428
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,080
Is the person in the photo

429
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:11,440
the photographer's boyfriend?

430
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:31,600
Jane?

431
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,640
You don't like it?

432
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:40,800
When I asked you before,

433
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,600
you said you liked every photo.

434
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:45,080
So I chose these.

435
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,600
I like the photos.

436
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,400
But I don't like

437
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:50,560
having my photos put on display

438
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,560
for everyone to look at without my consent.

439
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,280
And you even put a price on them.

440
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,800
Hey, but all the money goes to the club.

441
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,000
I'm not selling them commercially either.

442
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,240
Didn't it occur to you

443
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:04,400
that I'd feel like I was being priced?

444
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:12,280
I'm sorry.

445
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:15,600
I should've asked how you felt first.

446
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:18,280
I'll take responsibility for this.

447
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:21,200
I'll call the juniors and have the photos taken down.

448
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:30,960
What's up, P'Dan?

449
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:32,480
Hello, Hot.

450
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:34,480
I need a favor.

451
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:38,440
Take down all the photos in the portrait section.

452
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:39,280
I'm not exhibiting

453
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:40,400
and I'm not selling them anymore.

454
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:42,320
Too late, they're all sold out already.

455
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:43,320
What?

456
00:33:44,320 --> 00:33:45,200
Who bought them?

457
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:48,160
I'll head over.

458
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:54,800
Hey, make sure every single photo gets taken down.

459
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:56,080
Don't display that set anymore.

460
00:33:58,120 --> 00:33:58,720
Hot.

461
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,160
Oh, P'Dan.

462
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,640
Why do you want to take the photos down?

463
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,560
Will there be a problem

464
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:03,680
with the ones that were already sold?

465
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,080
Who bought them?

466
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,360
I'll tell them myself

467
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:08,360
that I'm not selling them anymore.

468
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,280
Uh...

469
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:10,159
It's me.

470
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,560
Yeah...

471
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:22,880
That makes me want to sell it even less.

472
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:27,520
I've already transferred the money.

473
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:28,880
The ownership belongs to me now.

474
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,360
Besides,

475
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,880
the sales agreement never said

476
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,920
I needed your permission.

477
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:36,159
You're unbelievable.

478
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:38,360
That mafia mentality of yours never changes.

479
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,120
I was just helping Jane.

480
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:45,080
You're unhappy about this, right?

481
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,960
Having your photos priced and sold

482
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:48,880
without being told first.

483
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:50,719
You put a price on my photos too.

484
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:53,719
If you don't want me to own the photos,

485
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:58,760
then let's make a contract.

486
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,640
I'll give them back.

487
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:13,920
You're not right for Jane at all.

488
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:16,640
Can you calm down for a second?

489
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,280
And are you really okay

490
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:21,600
with him taking your photos like that?

491
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,160
It's fine.

492
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,280
Whatever he wants to do with them

493
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:29,200
is his business.

494
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,040
Hey, Jane, but...

495
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:31,440
I said it's fine.

496
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:36,400
If you hadn't put my photos up for sale,

497
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,120
none of this would've happened.

498
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:47,280
I want to be alone for a while.

499
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:21,640
(Big Jane: Meet me at the fire escape.)

500
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:28,440
P'Jane.

501
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:31,680
P'Jane.

502
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:45,720
P'Jane.

503
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:49,960
Hey.

504
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:53,160
What are you doing?

505
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:55,800
I saw that you were feeling troubled,

506
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,600
so I helped you.

507
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,280
I didn't ask you to.

508
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:04,840
P'Dan was already going to take the photos down.

509
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:09,000
You should be thanking me.

510
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:13,520
If someone else had bought them instead of me,

511
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:16,720
what would you have done?

512
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:21,600
Anyone would've been better than you.

513
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:22,400
Why?

514
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:24,840
What do you think

515
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:26,640
I was going to do with your photos?

516
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:56,920
If you don't want me to keep them,

517
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:02,840
put your fingerprint here.

518
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,120
And I'll do what you want.

519
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,320
What's wrong with you?

520
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:17,520
Why are you always forcing people?

521
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,200
P'Jane.

522
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:22,360
Let go.

523
00:39:22,680 --> 00:39:23,600
I'm not forcing you.

524
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:27,160
You didn't have to come see me.

525
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:33,120
But you chose to come here.

526
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:44,880
Oh.

527
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:50,200
Are you sure you don't feel anything?

528
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:53,440
Ow.

529
00:39:58,640 --> 00:39:59,440
P'Jane, stop.

530
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:02,000
If you don't stop, I'm going to shout.

531
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:09,960
Has Dan ever made you feel this way?

532
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,040
Probably not.

533
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,200
Stop.

534
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:23,720
Stop.

535
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,120
If you don't stop, I'm really going to shout.

536
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:28,480
Then shout.

537
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:31,520
Let everyone, including Dan, come and see

538
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:36,200
what you and I are doing here.

539
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,960
You're hurting me.

540
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:46,560
Let go.

541
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:48,640
Let go.

542
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:51,560
It hurts.

543
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,040
Is this fun for you?

544
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,680
Do you think this is fun for me?

545
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,240
Jane.

546
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:48,600
Jane.

547
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:00,680
Jane.

548
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:02,480
What's wrong?

549
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:05,760
Nothing.

550
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:15,440
Was that him?

551
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:19,080
Did he do something to you?

552
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:23,520
Let's get out of here.

553
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:24,560
Jane, Jane.

554
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,120
Are you okay now?

555
00:42:52,360 --> 00:42:53,240
Yeah.

556
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:57,880
I think I'd better go home.

557
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:00,600
I'm sorry.

558
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,040
About the photos.

559
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,080
Forget it.

560
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:09,800
Let's not talk about it anymore.

561
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:14,400
Let me take you home.

562
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,080
No.

563
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:20,120
Jane.

564
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:33,120
I know this isn't the right moment,

565
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:38,000
but I want you to know something.

566
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:42,240
I've liked you for a long time.

567
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:56,800
Do you remember?

568
00:44:00,520 --> 00:44:02,320
My family went through a rough period.

569
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:05,120
I had to stop playing football for a while.

570
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:07,680
But I didn't want anyone to worry about me.

571
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:10,160
When I started playing again,

572
00:44:11,240 --> 00:44:12,920
I would secretly practice by myself.

573
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:15,040
But I couldn't get back into form.

574
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:20,720
Back then, I kept wondering

575
00:44:20,720 --> 00:44:22,520
if I should stop it all.

576
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:23,400
Football.

577
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,400
School.

578
00:44:25,600 --> 00:44:26,280
Everything.

579
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:34,160
You're P'Dan, right?

580
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:37,600
Yes.

581
00:44:37,960 --> 00:44:39,600
I heard you're coming back to football.

582
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:41,800
Keep it up.

583
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:44,360
I brought you some water.

584
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:48,000
We weren't very close.

585
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:50,040
You probably didn't think much of it.

586
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:50,840
Keep it up.

587
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:52,400
You were just encouraging me.

588
00:44:53,880 --> 00:44:55,000
But I've never forgotten

589
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,000
your encouragement that day.

590
00:44:58,320 --> 00:44:59,280
After that,

591
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:01,640
I kept watching you from afar.

592
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:10,920
Why are you telling me this now?

593
00:45:14,560 --> 00:45:16,320
Because I don't want to lose you.

594
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:26,520
Will you be my boyfriend?

595
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:44,560
I'm not ready to think about that right now.

596
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:50,720
But I'll think about it.

597
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:54,800
Then come and give you answer?

598
00:46:25,280 --> 00:46:25,800
You bastard!

599
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:26,360
Good job.

600
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:27,680
The finals are next round.

601
00:46:28,440 --> 00:46:29,080
Give it everything you've got.

602
00:46:29,240 --> 00:46:29,720
Come on.

603
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:30,760
Let's go.

604
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:32,240
Let's go, everyone.

605
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:32,720
Fight!

606
00:46:33,400 --> 00:46:34,400
One, two, three!

607
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:36,200
Business Faculty, let's go!!

608
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:38,640
Woooo!

609
00:46:38,640 --> 00:46:39,200
Let's go!

610
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:40,640
Let's go practice over there.

611
00:46:40,640 --> 00:46:42,120
Yeah, practice.

612
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:43,400
Let's go over there.

613
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:44,400
Come on.

614
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:45,000
Yeah.

615
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:45,920
Hey.

616
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:47,440
The football!

617
00:46:47,840 --> 00:46:49,520
Such a tiny football.

618
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:57,960
Oh.

619
00:46:57,960 --> 00:46:58,600
Come on!

620
00:47:21,640 --> 00:47:22,200
P'Jane.

621
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:23,840
Leave.

622
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,040
Can't you see everyone's practicing?

623
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:30,400
Do you really want me to leave?

624
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:35,160
If you're just here to cause trouble, then leave.

625
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:38,200
How can you tell me to leave?

626
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:41,200
Does this field belong to you?

627
00:47:41,720 --> 00:47:43,520
It doesn't belong to you either.

628
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:44,800
But I can buy it.

629
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:48,040
Then I can be the one kicking you out.

630
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:51,280
P'Jane.

631
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:52,880
Let go.

632
00:47:53,280 --> 00:47:54,080
Let go.

633
00:47:57,280 --> 00:47:58,480
If I want something,

634
00:47:59,560 --> 00:48:00,680
I always get it.

635
00:48:02,840 --> 00:48:04,000
Including you.

636
00:48:06,520 --> 00:48:07,640
Let go of Jane!!

637
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:09,480
P'Dan.

638
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:10,440
How are you?

639
00:48:11,160 --> 00:48:11,680
Ow.

640
00:48:12,680 --> 00:48:13,360
P'Jane!

641
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:16,720
What right do you have to tell me to let Jane go?

642
00:48:21,040 --> 00:48:22,120
P'Dan has every right.

643
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:29,880
P'Dan is my boyfriend.

644
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:36,520
Are you okay, P'Dan?

645
00:48:39,320 --> 00:48:40,520
Thank you, Jane.

646
00:48:45,680 --> 00:48:46,840
Let's go.

647
00:49:02,480 --> 00:49:03,000
Last night...

648
00:49:03,000 --> 00:49:03,520
Yeah.

649
00:49:04,160 --> 00:49:05,760
Wow.

650
00:49:41,960 --> 00:49:43,160
Our friend's really popular.

651
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:04,600
(Aren't you coming to the exam?)

652
00:50:17,040 --> 00:50:33,880
(Dan: What are you doing?)

653
00:50:33,880 --> 00:50:37,840
(Jane: Nothing, just lying around.)

654
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:38,000
Jane.

655
00:53:40,680 --> 00:53:41,600
Is something wrong?

656
00:53:45,480 --> 00:53:46,280
No.

657
00:53:47,320 --> 00:53:48,600
I was just spacing out.

658
00:53:56,560 --> 00:53:57,400
Give me your hand.

659
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:34,000
Thank you for the past month.

660
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,320
Has it already been a month?

661
00:54:39,800 --> 00:54:41,560
Time flies so fast.

662
00:54:48,760 --> 00:54:49,800
This is an amethyst.

663
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:53,840
The birthstone for people born on Saturday.

664
00:54:57,520 --> 00:54:59,040
Did I ever tell you

665
00:55:00,200 --> 00:55:02,520
I was born on a Saturday?

666
00:55:04,840 --> 00:55:06,680
I checked your Instagram.

667
00:55:07,240 --> 00:55:09,960
Then I looked back through the calendar.

668
00:55:14,160 --> 00:55:16,600
I was born on a Saturday too.

669
00:55:17,000 --> 00:55:18,280
I never knew

670
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:20,840
that you believed in things like this.

671
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:24,040
I don't really.

672
00:55:26,520 --> 00:55:28,360
But if we're born on the same day,

673
00:55:29,440 --> 00:55:31,760
it's kind of like wearing matching bracelets, right?

674
00:55:35,280 --> 00:55:36,480
Thank you, P'Dan.

675
00:55:40,200 --> 00:55:42,920
But I didn't prepare a gift for you.

676
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:46,480
That's okay.

677
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:53,920
But if I asked you for a gift,

678
00:55:57,480 --> 00:55:58,280
would that be alright?

679
00:56:44,640 --> 00:56:45,440
Hello?

680
00:56:51,320 --> 00:56:52,160
Really?

681
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:56,680
Okay, I'll head over right away.

682
00:56:58,840 --> 00:56:59,320
P'Dan.

683
00:56:59,840 --> 00:57:00,880
I have to go.

684
00:57:01,560 --> 00:57:02,040
Wait...

685
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:03,520
Sorry, I really have to go.

686
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,200
Jane, wait.

687
00:57:08,440 --> 00:57:09,480
Jet! Jet!

688
00:57:16,560 --> 00:57:17,160
P'Jane.

689
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:18,520
P'Jane.

690
00:57:18,520 --> 00:57:19,880
Jet, what happened?

691
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:30,280
What happened?

692
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:33,720
Please don't be mad at me.

693
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:38,400
I got into debt from football gambling.

694
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:41,400
And they came to collect.

695
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:44,720
When I told them I didn't have the money,

696
00:57:45,160 --> 00:57:47,280
they beat me up.

697
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:49,600
Debt?

698
00:57:52,880 --> 00:57:53,840
Since when?

699
00:57:55,040 --> 00:57:55,640
Is this why you wanted to

700
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:57,040
borrowed money from me?

701
00:57:58,800 --> 00:58:00,400
Forget about that.

702
00:58:01,160 --> 00:58:02,120
Right now,

703
00:58:03,240 --> 00:58:05,280
if I can't pay them,

704
00:58:06,360 --> 00:58:08,800
this won't end with just me getting beaten up.

705
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:11,800
Please help me.

706
00:58:13,280 --> 00:58:14,600
How much do you need?

707
00:58:16,360 --> 00:58:18,320
Fifty thousand, right? I'll transfer it to you.

708
00:58:19,080 --> 00:58:19,800
No..

709
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:23,800
P'Jane....

710
00:58:29,320 --> 00:58:30,120
1.2 million.

711
00:58:31,880 --> 00:58:32,880
1.2 million?!

712
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:38,000
Do you even realize what you've done?

713
00:58:43,880 --> 00:58:46,040
At first it wasn't this much.

714
00:58:48,160 --> 00:58:49,640
But I kept betting more.

715
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:51,040
I thought if I won,

716
00:58:51,040 --> 00:58:52,600
I could use it to pay off the old debt.

717
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:54,280
But I lost.

718
00:58:55,240 --> 00:58:56,200
I never thought

719
00:58:56,200 --> 00:58:58,480
the debt would grow this much.

720
00:59:02,680 --> 00:59:03,880
When do you have to pay it back?

721
00:59:06,040 --> 00:59:07,000
Tomorrow.

722
00:59:10,280 --> 00:59:11,080
Tomorrow?

723
00:59:14,960 --> 00:59:15,720
Where am I supposed to find

724
00:59:15,720 --> 00:59:17,280
that kind of money by tomorrow?

725
00:59:18,240 --> 00:59:20,440
No one's going to lend me that much money.

726
00:59:21,120 --> 00:59:21,920
P'Jane...

727
00:59:22,920 --> 00:59:24,000
What about him?

728
00:59:24,600 --> 00:59:25,640
Your ex!

729
00:59:26,960 --> 00:59:28,720
The one with all the supercars.

730
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:32,120
Can you ask him to help me?

731
00:59:32,600 --> 00:59:34,800
Please, I'm begging you.

732
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:36,760
Please help me.

733
00:59:36,760 --> 00:59:38,000
Calm down.

734
00:59:38,560 --> 00:59:40,240
Please, I'm begging you.

735
00:59:40,240 --> 00:59:41,040
Jet, calm down.

736
00:59:45,280 --> 00:59:47,040
(081-148-8776)

737
00:59:47,040 --> 00:59:47,760
P'Jane!

738
00:59:48,040 --> 00:59:49,600
They are calling again!

739
00:59:50,160 --> 00:59:50,800
P'Jane!

740
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:52,400
I'm too scared to answer!

741
00:59:52,600 --> 00:59:53,320
Okay.

742
01:00:12,080 --> 01:00:13,440
This is Jet, right?

743
01:00:14,920 --> 01:00:16,120
You know what'll happen

744
01:00:16,600 --> 01:00:17,840
if tomorrow comes

745
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:19,760
and you don't get my money.

746
01:00:20,120 --> 01:00:21,240
You know what'll happen, right?

747
01:00:22,680 --> 01:00:23,480
I'm Jane.

748
01:00:24,280 --> 01:00:25,280
Jet's older brother.

749
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:26,560
Oh? Is that so?

750
01:00:26,560 --> 01:00:28,560
Then come meet me behind the hospital.

751
01:00:30,200 --> 01:00:31,360
No!!

752
01:00:40,280 --> 01:00:42,360
When are you going to pay me back?

753
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:51,800
You're Jet's brother, right?

754
01:00:53,360 --> 01:00:54,200
You know exactly how much

755
01:00:54,200 --> 01:00:55,920
your brother owes me, don't you?

756
01:00:57,440 --> 01:00:58,640
It's almost the deadline.

757
01:00:58,640 --> 01:01:00,680
He has to give me back my money tomorrow.

758
01:01:01,320 --> 01:01:03,280
I really can't get that amount of money in time.

759
01:01:05,360 --> 01:01:06,120
Could you please...

760
01:01:07,200 --> 01:01:08,440
give me an extension?

761
01:01:09,400 --> 01:01:11,080
I'll pay in installments if I have to.

762
01:01:13,040 --> 01:01:13,880
Installments?

763
01:01:15,640 --> 01:01:16,440
Installments?

764
01:01:16,680 --> 01:01:18,920
Boss Jeng is a very kind man.

765
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:23,800
I'll be charging extra interest.

766
01:01:23,800 --> 01:01:25,920
And I'll be taking one of Jet's

767
01:01:26,280 --> 01:01:27,600
fingers each day.

768
01:01:28,320 --> 01:01:29,280
One finger a day.

769
01:01:29,280 --> 01:01:30,400
Until all ten are gone.

770
01:01:31,320 --> 01:01:32,880
And when all ten fingers are gone,

771
01:01:33,360 --> 01:01:35,080
I'll start breaking his arms.

772
01:01:35,320 --> 01:01:36,120
Then his legs.

773
01:01:36,560 --> 01:01:37,960
I'll break every last part of him.

774
01:01:38,720 --> 01:01:39,520
How about that?

775
01:01:41,720 --> 01:01:43,280
If you touch Jet,

776
01:01:44,440 --> 01:01:45,400
I'll go to the police.

777
01:01:45,760 --> 01:01:48,040
If you're planning to report me,

778
01:01:48,040 --> 01:01:50,880
send my regards to the officers at the station.

779
01:01:51,800 --> 01:01:52,960
Because at the station

780
01:01:53,400 --> 01:01:56,200
they all know who Boss Jeng is.

781
01:01:57,000 --> 01:01:58,160
Because Boss Jeng

782
01:01:58,800 --> 01:02:01,880
takes very good care of all of them.

783
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:08,440
By the way,

784
01:02:09,600 --> 01:02:11,520
I heard your family's pretty cute.

785
01:02:12,480 --> 01:02:14,960
A small Chinese medicine shop.

786
01:02:15,600 --> 01:02:17,400
In a little alley, right?

787
01:02:18,320 --> 01:02:19,400
Maybe when I'm not busy

788
01:02:20,080 --> 01:02:21,600
I'll drop by sometime.

789
01:02:22,800 --> 01:02:24,560
Don't drag my family into this!

790
01:02:24,560 --> 01:02:25,080
Ow!

791
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:29,240
I told you,

792
01:02:29,560 --> 01:02:31,160
don't raise your voice at me.

793
01:02:31,400 --> 01:02:33,760
I get startled very easily.

794
01:02:34,600 --> 01:02:35,200
You!!

795
01:02:36,360 --> 01:02:36,960
Ow!

796
01:02:48,520 --> 01:02:50,080
Like I said,

797
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:53,120
I get startled easily.

798
01:02:53,560 --> 01:02:55,160
Let me give you

799
01:02:56,480 --> 01:02:58,000
one final warning!

800
01:02:58,640 --> 01:03:00,240
If you don't want your home destroyed,

801
01:03:00,400 --> 01:03:03,720
you'd better get my money by tomorrow!

802
01:03:03,720 --> 01:03:04,520
Understand?!

803
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:09,160
But...

804
01:03:11,960 --> 01:03:13,080
Can I please ask for more time?

805
01:03:15,240 --> 01:03:17,800
I swear I'll find the money and pay you back.

806
01:03:18,200 --> 01:03:19,800
Please give me a bit more time.

807
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:25,400
Fine.

808
01:03:26,160 --> 01:03:27,320
But I think

809
01:03:28,200 --> 01:03:29,440
it's about time

810
01:03:29,760 --> 01:03:31,600
your family's shop closed down.

811
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:34,920
Because tomorrow...

812
01:03:35,080 --> 01:03:35,680
Ow!

813
01:03:35,680 --> 01:03:37,160
it's going to be

814
01:03:37,680 --> 01:03:39,120
completely destroyed!!

815
01:03:39,120 --> 01:03:40,520
Ow!

816
01:03:41,880 --> 01:03:44,400
Finish him off.

817
01:03:48,560 --> 01:03:51,680
Ugh!

818
01:03:56,280 --> 01:04:01,160
Aah!

819
01:05:05,360 --> 01:05:06,480
Ow!

820
01:05:06,480 --> 01:05:07,640
Hey!

821
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:09,440
Do you have a fucking death wish?!

822
01:05:54,440 --> 01:05:56,520
Why were you walking in the rain?

823
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:02,480
What happened to your face?

824
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:17,400
Let me get you a towel.

825
01:06:21,040 --> 01:06:22,160
P'Jane.

826
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:37,680
I need to ask something from you.

827
01:06:52,920 --> 01:06:53,720
You're asking

828
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:58,040
for a favour?

829
01:07:03,000 --> 01:07:05,360
Jet owes money from football gambling.

830
01:07:07,480 --> 01:07:09,200
1.2 million

831
01:07:11,160 --> 01:07:12,000
The debt collectors are going to

832
01:07:12,000 --> 01:07:13,600
destroy my family.

833
01:07:16,800 --> 01:07:19,320
Can you clear the debt for me?

834
01:07:41,000 --> 01:07:43,680
Are you in your right mind right now?

835
01:07:46,520 --> 01:07:49,200
You're sure you want to do this contract with me?

836
01:07:53,080 --> 01:07:55,880
The deal where I can ask for anything in return?

837
01:07:59,440 --> 01:08:00,360
Yes.

838
01:08:02,480 --> 01:08:03,400
I'll do it.

839
01:09:44,439 --> 01:09:46,240
Then our agreement...

840
01:09:47,600 --> 01:09:49,359
is complete.

841
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:10,320
Let's talk about out contract.

842
01:10:10,320 --> 01:10:11,360
The first rule

843
01:10:11,360 --> 01:10:13,760
is don't be too emotional.

844
01:10:13,760 --> 01:10:14,880
The second rule is

845
01:10:14,880 --> 01:10:16,600
You said you'll belong only to me.

846
01:10:17,200 --> 01:10:18,640
But words aren't enough.

847
01:10:18,640 --> 01:10:20,080
You have to show me too.

848
01:10:20,400 --> 01:10:21,800
Let's break up.

849
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:23,960
You didn't really want to break up with me, right?

850
01:10:23,960 --> 01:10:26,400
I won't let them force you.

851
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:27,840
In the end,

852
01:10:28,240 --> 01:10:29,360
you still chose this.

853
01:10:29,360 --> 01:10:31,520
Do you even see me as a friend?

854
01:10:52,200 --> 01:10:57,000
You walk in with a warning sign

855
01:10:59,080 --> 01:11:04,200
Just one look and already falling for you

856
01:11:06,480 --> 01:11:11,600
My friends tell me not to cross that line

857
01:11:13,560 --> 01:11:18,680
But I’m already out of time

858
01:11:20,480 --> 01:11:22,560
I know the truth, I taste the sin

859
01:11:22,560 --> 01:11:24,120
It’s wrong but I don’t want it to be true

860
01:11:24,120 --> 01:11:26,800
I’m losing all my discipline

861
01:11:26,800 --> 01:11:30,800
You’re all I’m thinking of

862
01:11:30,800 --> 01:11:32,920
and I’m breaking all the rules

863
01:11:32,920 --> 01:11:35,200
just because…

864
01:11:35,200 --> 01:11:38,520
You’re a red flag but I’m colorblind

865
01:11:38,520 --> 01:11:41,880
I know you’re dangerous

866
01:11:42,400 --> 01:11:45,760
If it burns, let it burn me alive

867
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:49,680
I can't hold myself back, I’d cross every line

868
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:53,000
You’re a red flag but I’m colorblind

869
01:11:53,000 --> 01:11:56,600
I’d give up anything for you

870
01:11:56,600 --> 01:12:00,200
Even if it burns, I'm willing to melt away

871
01:12:00,200 --> 01:12:05,120
I can't hold myself back, I’d cross every line

872
01:12:10,200 --> 01:12:11,640
Ooh

873
01:12:11,640 --> 01:12:14,880
You can paint me with all your darkest sides

874
01:12:14,880 --> 01:12:18,480
And I’d still wear them like they’re paradise

875
01:12:18,480 --> 01:12:22,080
If this love is a perfect crime

876
01:12:22,080 --> 01:12:26,000
Then I’m guilty for life

877
01:12:26,000 --> 01:12:26,680
You tell me,

